<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id79fa3b92-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s5011"><num value="5011">§ 5011.</num><heading> Funding requirements</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id79fa3b93-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s5011/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Authorization</heading><chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated from time to time such sums as may be necessary for carrying out the purposes and provisions of the Convention and this chapter, including—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id79fa3b94-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s5011/a/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> necessary travel expenses of the United States Commissioners or Alternate Commissioners; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id79fa3b95-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s5011/a/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> the United States’ share of the joint expenses of the Commission.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id79fa3b96-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s5011/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Research</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Such funds as shall be made available to the Secretary of Commerce for research and related activities shall be expended to carry out the program of the Commission in accordance with the recommendations of the United States Section and to carry out other research and observer programs pursuant to the Convention.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id79fa3b97-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/102/567/tVIII/s812">Pub. L. 102–567, title VIII, § 812</ref>, <date date="1992-10-29">Oct. 29, 1992</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/106/4316">106 Stat. 4316</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/102/587/tVIII/s8012">Pub. L. 102–587, title VIII, § 8012</ref>, <date date="1992-11-04">Nov. 4, 1992</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/106/5105">106 Stat. 5105</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/106/562/tIII/s304/a">Pub. L. 106–562, title III, § 304(a)</ref>, <date date="2000-12-23">Dec. 23, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/2806">114 Stat. 2806</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id79fa3b98-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id79fa3b99-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id79fa3b9a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Title VIII of <ref href="/us/pl/102/567">Pub. L. 102–567</ref> and <ref href="/us/pl/102/587">Pub. L. 102–587</ref> enacted substantially identical sections. Title VIII of <ref href="/us/pl/102/587">Pub. L. 102–587</ref> was repealed by <ref href="/us/pl/106/562">Pub. L. 106–562</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
